originalText.text: I arrived to pick up a Zipcar this morning after another garage had misplaced the keys of my originally assigned vehicle. My newly assigned vehicle was not parked with the Zipcars. It was in the back. Engine running. The only parking attendant in the garage is asleep in my car. He burned all the gas. The gauge was pegged on E. Made it to the closest gas station on fumes and a prayer.

originalText.text: Parking attendant misplaced our keys. Turns out it was dropped in someone else' car. We eventually got it back. However, we were told by management that they would make it right. The gentleman instructed us to take a cab and that they will reimburse the expenses. It's been two weeks and management has been dodging our calls. If this was middle of the day and if we had somewhere important to go, we would've lost our jobs on top of losing our sanity. We would've forgiven the fact the keys were lost and our day was ruined, but management adding insult to injury is not very cool. Bring an extra key when parking here or just don't park here. You've been warned.

originalText.text: Manager Sanon is very nice. All the staff are great. Please tip them hahah The space is small and always only 1 person working so there is a bit of a delay when you go during the typical 8am/7PM hours. But they offer convenient monthly enrollment online so I just needed to Google it/register and show up the next day. It did take about 30 days for the car tag to mail to my house though. This is the second closest garage to my work but much better for me than the one on 29th and 2nd ave because of pricing issues at the other one
